<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
~sigh~<BR>How I start a Sorcerer:<BR>The way things are set up now, put NO points into matter. Keep Mind up to about 75-80% of your level, and dump everything else into Body. This will guarantee you a good pet with no hastles. When you get 20 in Mind (can get the most variety of pets up to level 40), stop putting points into it and start putting all your points into Body, untill you're at 20 Mind and 22 Body (22 Body has a great DD)<P>You'll want to get 2 Bracers of Magic as soon as possible for the extra 4 Points to your Mind skill, to keep your effective Mind up high enough that the pets won't resist Charm. Make sure you complete the level 25 Guild Quest (I think 25) for the Thought Threaded cloak for one more point into Mind.<P>Ok once you reach level 30 or so you'll have 20 mind and 22 in Body. At this point dump all the points you get into Mind untill level 40, or you get to 32 in Mind so you have the final charm and can get level 40-50 Pets. Start dumping all your points after this into Body till you get the second Best DD, plus the AOE version of the Body Spec Root. (You'll almost be to 50 at this point). Then pop another point (or is 2?) into Mind for the 2nd best AOE mes. Once you have that Mes, dump all your leftover pionts into Body.<P>End result: 2nd Best AOE Mes. 2nd Best Body Spec DD. AOE Root. Right now at 36 My Pendragon Sorcerer is on track and VERRY happy. With the Confusion you get at level 34 you'll find you can solo low reds semi-consistantly. And Ornges will be your bread and butter. You'll have all the tools for grouping, and your DD's will be strong enough to earn some RPs outside of your pet in RVR. =)<P>--------------------<P>Albion Bedvedere Server:<BR>Jerid DeGray Lev 39 Cleric-500 Armorcrafter<BR>Nevyl Mindweaver Lev 31 Sorcerer- 600 Tailor (Kniting needles rule!)<BR>Garvin Brightshield Lev 17 Paladin-400 Weaponcrafter<BR>Solari Earthsinger Lev 20 Theurgist-0 Spellcrafter <P>Pendragon Clone:<BR>Nevyl Mindweaver Lev 36 Sorcerer- 600 Tailor (Cloned Kniting needles rule too!)<BR>"Ok they threw out our epic vests  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> we're doomed to wearing <B>Wizard</B> dresses now"
