<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
There are a lot of good reasons for double speccing, for one, the level 35 spec dd is a LOT better than the base lifedrain. 22 more points of base damage means 45+ when you blast even cons in rvr, and with all the resists and ways to screw casters, you need every point you can get if you want to be able to kill something. <P>Having your body skill that high results in a near zero variance blasting things at your level, which is another way to get those extra damage points, and even more should you eventually pass 50 in skill which isn't hard between items and realm ranks.<P>You usually don't lose as much damage to resist from the spec nuke as you do the base drain, look at some screenshots and see the negatives from the base drain then look at someone using mind shriek.<P>The nuke isn't the only good body spell you get speccing that high, getting into the mid 30's gives you the second level of resist debuffs, and the level 39 ae root is a full minute duration, which is a nice improvement over the 46 seconds of the level 30 one.<P>And last but not least, until matter is fixed, there's really nothing else worth putting your spec points into anyways. The only argument i would ever make right now for 44 mind is if the mez timer gets removed and we can actually start mezzing people and have it stick again. But until that day, you may as well diversify.<P>--------------------<P>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Sorceress of 47 seasons on Percival
</FONT>
